<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-05-08T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-05-08T10:00:00-05:00" n="823" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d823">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">818.6363/114: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Costa Rica</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Davis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">San
                                        José</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-05-08T09:00:00-06:00"><hi rend="italic">May 8, 1922—9
                                        a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 7:30
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>18. Your May 5, 3 p.m. Local representative greatly desires that
                            representations be made but hesitates to request same on account of the
                            provision in the contract which stipulates that in no case can
                            contractor revert to diplomatic channels. If under these circumstances
                            Department desires this Legation to make the opportune representation
                            outlined in the above-mentioned cablegram please instruct
                            immediately.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>